Spatial Analysis-Secrets of the Supermarket

Jennifer Flores
Sep 5
10 points
Due Tomorrow, 9:00 AM
Add class comment
*In class, we read the article, "Secrets of the Supermarket" to understand how space is used to market and accommodate the consumer.
1. Choose a store, mall, or amusement park to analyze how the space is used.

2. Take notes and diagram the space or layout of the space that you have chosen. You can draw on the back of the handout provided or draw on a piece of paper and attach it to the handout when you turn it in.
3. 10 "secrets" were revealed in the article read in class. Choose at least 7 of the elements that are discussed in the article. In the handout provided, analyze how the space and elements that you chose to discuss are designed to market and provide access to accommodate consumers or visitors. 
-Consider the demographics and clientele of the store and the types of goods and/or services provided.
-Consider using ESPeN in drawing conclusions of your spatial analysis.
-How does the use of space affect marketing of products while appealing to various subgroups of people. Consider location placement of goods and services.

An amusement park

A large mall

A grocery store

Identify 7 elements/components of your choice (bathrooms, shopping area, fountains, etc.) and then

describe its spatial expression (think: locations, distribution/clustering, distances, orientations, patterns,

5. Traffic builder

Ever wondered why milk and bread are always way at the back of the store? The theory goes that placing

essentials away from the entrance means we are exposed to more potential purchases and offers on the way.

Scamell-Kanj eeach ho hee diaction tactics can be fraught because shoppers arrive at a store with a

entrance made shoppers more likely to return to the main store for their weekly shop.
